# Card-audit (mtg-948 Part B): Pyroclasm — 2 damage to each creature (scripted).
#
# Closed issue mtg-851 closed Pyroclasm as WORKING but carried NO scripted
# puzzle with semantic assertions. This audit puzzle SCRIPTS the cast and asserts
# the symmetric board-sweep outcome.
#
# Pyroclasm is a {1}{R} sorcery: "Pyroclasm deals 2 damage to each creature."
# (A:SP$ DamageAll | NumDmg$ 2 | ValidCards$ Creature). DamageAll is symmetric:
# it hits EVERY creature on the battlefield, regardless of controller. Any
# creature with toughness <= 2 dies from lethal damage (CR 704.5g).
#
# Aspects exercised (issue mtg-851):
#   1. Parses + castable as a {1}{R} sorcery (spell cast assertion).
#   2. DamageAll deals 2 to EACH creature symmetrically (both players').
#   3. A 2/2 (P0's own Grizzly Bears) and a 1/1 (P1's Savannah Lions, here used
#      as a 2/1-toughness-1 creature) both take 2 and die; a 3/3 (P1's Hill
#      Giant, toughness 3) survives with 2 damage marked.
#
# Scenario:
#   - P0: Pyroclasm in hand, 1 Mountain + 1 Forest to pay {1}{R}; a 2/2 Grizzly
#     Bears it controls (dies to its own sweep — symmetric).
#   - P1: a Savannah Lions (2/1, dies) and a Hill Giant (3/3, survives).
#   - Script: P0 casts Pyroclasm; both 2-or-less-toughness creatures die, the
#     3/3 survives.

[metadata]
Name:Card Audit - Pyroclasm Sweeps the Board
Goal:Win
Turns:1
Difficulty:Easy
Description:P0 scripts Pyroclasm ({1}{R} sorcery), dealing 2 to EACH creature. P0's own 2/2 Grizzly Bears and P1's 2/1 Savannah Lions die; P1's 3/3 Hill Giant survives. Backs issue mtg-851 (symmetric SP$ DamageAll NumDmg$ 2 ValidCards$ Creature; CR 704.5g).

[state]
turn=1
activeplayer=p0
activephase=MAIN1
p0life=20
p0hand=Pyroclasm
p0battlefield=Mountain;Forest;Grizzly Bears
p0library=Mountain;Mountain;Mountain;Mountain;Mountain

p1life=20
p1battlefield=Savannah Lions;Hill Giant
p1library=Forest;Forest;Forest;Forest;Forest

[p0_script]
# Cast Pyroclasm; it deals 2 to every creature on the board (no targets — it is
# a DamageAll sweep, so a plain cast suffices). Then PASS for the rest of the
# game so neither side plays new creatures that would muddy the survivor check.
cast Pyroclasm
PASS_UNTIL turn=5,phase=MAIN1

[p1_script]
# P1 takes no proactive action (keeps the surviving Hill Giant in place).
PASS_UNTIL turn=5,phase=MAIN1

[assertions]
# The sweeper sorcery was actually cast.
spell cast Pyroclasm
# P0's own 2/2 died to the symmetric sweep (proves it is NOT one-sided).
creature died Grizzly Bears
# P1's 2/1 died too.
creature died Savannah Lions
# Both dead creatures rest in their owners' graveyards (durable end-state).
graveyard contains Grizzly Bears
opponent graveyard contains Savannah Lions
# The 3/3 Hill Giant survived the 2-damage sweep (2 < 3 toughness): it never
# died (durable — the event log records no death for it).
NOT creature died Hill Giant
